description:
Hong Kong based company with more than 20 years experience in bag manufacturing URGENTLY requires in our Kwun Tong office:

Accounting & Admin. Officer

Responsibilities:

Daily accounting operations including general journal entries, payments, petty cash, staff reimbursement, preparing monthly reports, etc.
General office administrative work
Managing staff attendance and leave record
Ad-hoc assignments

Requirements:

Min. 2 years experience; Fresh graduate will be considered;
Diploma in accounting;
Proficient in MS Office, Chinese Word Processing;
Prior experience with ERP is an advantage;
Good spoken & written English, Chinese & Mandarin;
Able to work independently, responsible, self-motivated, hardworking & eager to learn;
Immediate available is preferred.

Interested parties please send resume with salary expected to Jibsen Industrial Ltd by pressing APPLY NOW

(Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Responsibilities:

Perform accounting functions including Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable and Invoicing, etc.;
Handle administrative work including preparation of payment vouchers and cheque;
Maintain accounting records and perform data entry;
Assist in ad-hoc assignments;
Other duties assigned by supervisor

Requirements:

Diploma or above qualification in accounting or LCCI Intermediate above preferred;
With 2 years or above relevant experiences, prefer Property Management field;
Proficiency in MS office application & Chinese WordProcessing;
Proficient in Cantonese and English;
Independent, stable, attentive to details, multi-tasking, able to work under pressure and adaptive to given challenges;
Immediate available is highly preferable

Method to Apply:

l  Interested parties please submit your application with expected salaries and availability to Ec InfoTech Ltd Human Resources Department by clicking to Apply Now.

l   Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only and Applicants who are not invited to interview within 2 months may consider their applicants unsuccessful.

Responsibilities

Handle full set accounting and month end closing;
Prepare full set of accounts including general ledger, accounts receivable and accounts payable;
Prepare management reports and financial analysis on a timely basis;
Assist in reviewing Taiwan and Macau companies’ management reports;
Assist in annual audit, final accounts and budget;
Other ad hoc tasks as assigned.

Requirements

Degree holder in Accounting, Finance or related discipline;
5 years relevant experience;
Familiar with MS office, particularly in MS Excel and word;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Self-motivated, detail oriented, strong sense of responsibility and multi-tasked;
Good interpersonal, communication, analytical and problem-solving skills;
Good communication in both English, Chinese and Mandarin.

主要負責香港會計全盤賬目.
工作包括處理日常如系統資料輸入等, 應收,應付, 出糧, 銀行查帳/對帳 和 總帳;
需安排每月結算, 銷售佣金, 分析報表, 報銷單據, 全套帳戶, 財務報告和總帳;
需不定時與會計師溝通完成每年審計及主管委派之工作.
另需處理日常行政事務, 採購和進出口報關.

Key Responsibilities:

Perform data input into ERP Accounting & Retail system;  
Mainly responsible for A/P section, bills settlement & maintain bank books;
Assist in preparing various simple reports, accounting schedules and bank reconciliation;
Full set of account experience is definite advantage;
Perform other ad hoc tasks as assigned.

 Job Requirements:

F.5 with LCCI Inter or above;
At least 5 years’ solid experience in accounting or auditing;
Experience in Accounting & ERP system is a definite advantage;
Retail accounting experience is definite advantage;
Strong sense of responsibility, hardworking and willing to LEARN;
Proficiency in MS office, especially Excel spreadsheet & outlook;
Quick typing skill on both Chinese and English;
Immediately available is highly preferred.

We offer permanent job with basically 5-day work per week, excellent career opportunities and remuneration package to the right candidates. Interested parties please apply with detailed resume, salary expected, contact numbers in strict confidence and quoting reference in your application by clicking “Apply Now”.

All information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for recruitment purposes.  Candidates without salary expectation will not be considered.

