“K” Line Logistics (Hong Kong) Limited is a global logistics company offering total logistics solution including air and ocean freight, land transport and distribution etc.  Our headquarters is based in Japan and our international network links more than 150 countries and cities worldwide. To cope with our expansion, we are inviting high caliber professional for the following position:

ASSISTANT ACCOUNTANT 
 
(Working location: Lai Chi Kok)

This position will be responsible to handle daily bank operations including payment & receipt vouchers as well as autopay arrangement, bank reconciliation, book-keeping, staff reimbursement. You are required to handle some ad hoc jobs.


Requirements:

Form 5 / DSE or above, Diploma or above in Accounting discipline;
LCCI higher / ACCA level 1 or above;
At least 1 year accounting experience in which exposure in freight forwarder industry is an advantage;
Good in spoken and written English and Chinese, Mandarin speaking is an advantage;
Good computer skills with MS Office, Flex Accounting is preferable;
Strong in communication and problem solving skills;
Detailed minded, reliable, self-motivated and team player;
Immediate available preferred

We offer attractive fringe benefits which include 5 days work-week, Double Pay, Performance Bonus, Training Allowances, Overtime Allowances, Medical & Dental Scheme, Mandatory Provident Fund and 12-21 days Annual Leave.

If you are interested in this position, please send application with detailed qualifications, experience, current and expected salary by click “Apply Now” to submit your application.

(All information provided are kept confidential and all personal data provided will be used for the recruitment purpose only)

RESPONSIBILITIES
Assist in carrying out daily accounting activities including trust account maintenance, daily FRR preparation etc.;
Responsible for the preparation of full set of accounts for brokerage business ;
Responsible for the preparation of monthly financial reports and management reports;
Assist in the preparation of full set of accounts for the group’s proprietary trading business; and
Process monthly accounting schedules;
Process daily/monthly payment

 REQUIREMENTS

Accounting degree holder;
Minimum 2 years relevant experience in leading securities brokers or relevant audit experience in CPA firms;
Proficient in Epicor Accounting software;
Good understanding of accounting knowledge;
Good command of written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Willing to take up new tasks and assignments;
Good communication skill;
Immediate available is preferred.
Candidate with less experience will be considered for the post of Assistant Accounts Officer.

 A competitive remuneration package will be offered. Please send your detailed resume, including present and expected salary as well as availability date, to Human Resources Department, SinoPac Securities (Asia) Limited, 7/F., Lee Garden Three, 1 Sunning Road, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong or by clicking “Apply Now”. 

All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only and will be kept strictly confidential. Only short-listed candidates will be notified.

Responsibilities:

Handle full set accounts and daily accounting operation independently;
Prepare month end closing and financial report;
Assist in the financial forecast on a monthly basis and financial budgeting on a yearly basis;
Handle regular administrative office works;
Participate in ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements:

Diploma or above in accounting or similar;
3 years or above accounting / finance experience, of which with PRC accounting and listed company experience is highly preferred;
Self-motivated, well organized, independent, responsible, able to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines;
Proficiency in MS Excel. Experiences in using accounting system such as EBS are preferred;
Strong command in both spoken and written in English and Chinese (both Mandarin & Cantonese);
Occasionally travel to Mainland China is required; and
Immediate available is preferred.

Reporting to the Senior Accountant, the incumbent will be responsible for accounts payable & receivable, preparation of vouchers & simple accounting analysis, assisting in month end closing and other ad hoc assignments.

Requirements:
Higher diploma or above in Accounting or related discipline;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Good interpersonal skills;
Self-motivated with analytical mind;
Fresh university graduates will also be considered.

Working location: Tsuen Wan

Benefits:
We offer competitive remuneration package including annual leave, discretionary bonus, dental and medical coverage and Top-up MPF. We value our employees’ career development and provide them with a variety of internal and external training opportunities.

Application Methods:

Online application – Visit our website http://www.hkri.com (Career Opportunities/ Hong Kong Resort Company Limited) to complete the online application form;
Email – Send your detailed resume and expected salary to "Apply Now";
Whatsapp – 5987 0673;
Fax – 2902 2510
